# NEGATIVE (card aabf4ada): sum() takes at most 2 arguments — `sum(iterable[, start])`.
# A 3rd positional arg is a CPython TypeError. pyrst (whose `sum` is variadic-exempt
# from the generic arity check) formerly ACCEPTED extra args and silently dropped
# them at codegen; it now rejects this at CHECK time, keeping typeck acceptance and
# codegen consumption in exact agreement.
def main() -> None:
    print(sum([1, 2, 3], 10, 20))
